docs.lead_paragraph: Infant mortality has declined nationwide by 11 percent since 2006, but the mortality rate for fetuses in the second half of pregnancy has stalled, the report says.

headline.main: Stillbirths Now Outnumber Deaths Among Infants, Study Finds
headline.print_headline: Stillbirths Outnumber Infant Deaths, New Study Finds

docs.abstract: National Center for Health Statistics study finds that stillbirths have slightly outnumbered infant deaths for first time, with 23,595 stillbirths in 2013, compared with 23,446 infant deaths before first birthday.
